.TH TERMIDORO 1 "January 2026" "Termidoro 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
termidoro \- terminal pomodoro timer

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B termidoro
.RI [OPTIONS]
.RI [work-duration]
.RI [break-duration]
.RI [custom-name]

.SH DESCRIPTION
termidoro is a terminal-based Pomodoro timer that helps you manage time and maintain focus during work sessions. It features a responsive UI that adapts to terminal resizing, progress visualization with gradient colors, sound notifications, and comprehensive session tracking.

The application implements the Pomodoro Technique® using work/break cycles to break down work into focused intervals separated by short breaks.

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.BR \-m " \fIminutes\fP"
Set default work duration in minutes. Default is 25 minutes.
If positional arguments are also provided, the last specified value takes precedence.

.TP
.BR \-y
Enable auto-confirm mode for scripting and automation. When enabled, the timer will automatically continue to the next cycle without prompting the user.

.SH POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS

.TP
.I work-duration
Duration for work sessions. Can be specified as:
- Number (e.g., 25) - interpreted as minutes
- With time unit (e.g., 25m, 1h30m, 90s)
Default: 25 minutes

.TP
.I break-duration
Duration for break sessions. Follows the same format as work-duration.
Default: 5 minutes

.TP
.I custom-name
Optional custom name for work sessions. Useful for tracking different types of activities.
Default: "WORK"

.SH EXAMPLES

Basic usage with default settings:
.PP
.RS
$ termidoro
.RE

Custom 30-minute work, 10-minute break cycles:
.PP
.RS
$ termidoro 30 10
.RE

With custom session name:
.PP
.RS
$ termidoro 25 5 "Feature Development"
.RE

Long sessions with mixed time units:
.PP
.RS
$ termidoro 2h 30m "Planning Session"
.RE

Automated mode for scripting:
.PP
.RS
$ termidoro -y 25 5
.RE

.SH CONTROLS

During active sessions:
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Cancel the current session and display a recap of completed sessions.

Between sessions (interactive mode):
.TP
.B Y
Continue to the next session.
.TP
.B N
End the timer and show session recap.

.SH OUTPUT FORMAT

The timer interface displays:
.nf
Line 1: [WORK Cycle N]
Line 2: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
Line 3: │ [progress bar]          X:XX left │
Line 4: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
Line 5: Messages (Time for a break!, etc.)
Line 6: Prompts (Continue with another cycle? [Y/n])
.fi

Session recap format:
.nf
--- Session Recap ---
1. 25m 00 - 09:00 - 09:25 ✓
2. 5m 00 - 09:25 - 09:30 ✓
3. 25m 00 - 09:30 - 09:55 ✓
Total: 55m 00s
.fi

